And this was seen as part of his preparations to claim the throne should President Cyril Ramaphosa appoint him over King Misuzulu. The wedding celebrations started with umembeso and umkhehlo before the couple exchanged vows before Reverend Celinhlanhla Mthethwa at Mtubatuba, KZN on Saturday, 8 January. According to Zulu culture, a king should get married first before he leads the Zulu nation and both King Misuzulu and Prince Simakade are now both married.  But Prince Simakade Zulu told the People’s Paper Londiwe’s respect led to him marrying her. Londiwe said: “I appreciate all the things he has done for me. He is my best friend.” 